					<msContents class="#MTM">
						<summary><p>Multiple-text manuscript containing two poems in praise of the Goddess:
							<list
								rend="numbered">
								<item>The <title xml:lang="ta"
									>Apirāmi Antāti</title> in 101 stanzas (U1a and U1b: <foreign
										xml:lang="ta"
										>kāppu</foreign> + stanzas 1-100). A work by <persName
											xml:lang="ta" role="author"
											>Apirāma Paṭṭar</persName> (Zvelebil 1995, p. 50).</item>
								<item>The <title xml:lang="ta"
									>Ampikaimālai</title> in 30 stanzas (U2a and U2b: <foreign
										xml:lang="ta"
										>kāppu</foreign> + stanzas 1-29); A work by <persName
											xml:lang="ta" role="author"
											>Kulacēkara Varakuṇa Rāma Pāṇṭiyaṉ</persName> (Zvelebil 1995, p. 370).</item>
							</list></p>
							<p>Description based on the examination of the original manuscript (May 2021).</p>
							<p>Dimensions assessed at the time of examination.</p>
						</summary>
						
